-- Spanjaard of South Africa First-Half Net Income Surges as Revenue Climbs
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-10-28T04:45:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/spanjaard-of-south-africa-first-half-net-income-surges-as-revenue-climbs.html
Spanjaard Ltd., a South African
lubricant manufacturer, said first-half profit surged as sales
increased.  Net income jumped to 2.24 million rand ($318,303) in the
six months through August from 117,000 rand in the same period a
year earlier, according to a statement published in the
Johannesburg-based Business Day newspaper today. Revenue climbed
19 percent to 48.5 million rand, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  